# üîê Domain 3Ô∏è‚É£ ‚Äî Secure Software Development

Security is a **non-negotiable domain** in enterprise systems.
It‚Äôs built into every layer of SDLC ‚Äî from **code to build pipeline**.

---

### ‚öôÔ∏è Security Lifecycle (SSDLC ‚Äì Secure Software Development Life Cycle)

| Stage              | Focus                          | Tools / Practices                |
| ------------------ | ------------------------------ | -------------------------------- |
| **Requirements**   | Identify security requirements | Threat modeling, STRIDE          |
| **Design**         | Define security architecture   | Secure data flow diagrams        |
| **Implementation** | Code securely                  | OWASP Top 10 guidelines          |
| **Testing**        | Automated static/dynamic scans | Fortify, SonarQube, WebInspect   |
| **Deployment**     | Secure configuration           | HTTPS, encryption, IAM           |
| **Monitoring**     | Runtime security               | DynaTrace, JProfiler, CloudWatch |

---

### üß† Key Secure Coding Practices

1. **Input Validation:** Always sanitize user input (avoid SQL injection, XSS).
2. **Authentication & Authorization:** Use Spring Security + JWT.
3. **Encryption:** Store passwords using BCrypt; use HTTPS.
4. **Error Handling:** No stack traces or sensitive info in responses.
5. **Dependency Scanning:** Use **NexusIQ** to block vulnerable libraries.
6. **Static Code Analysis:** Use **HP Fortify** to catch flaws before build.
7. **Dynamic Scanning:** Use **WebInspect** for runtime penetration testing.

---

### ‚úÖ Example: Secure Spring Boot REST API

```java
@EnableWebSecurity
public class SecurityConfig extends WebSecurityConfigurerAdapter {

    @Override
    protected void configure(HttpSecurity http) throws Exception {
        http.csrf().disable()
            .authorizeRequests()
            .antMatchers("/api/public/**").permitAll()
            .antMatchers("/api/admin/**").hasRole("ADMIN")
            .anyRequest().authenticated()
            .and()
            .oauth2ResourceServer()
            .jwt();
    }
}
```

**SonarQube + Fortify Scan Integration (Maven):**

```xml
<plugin>
    <groupId>org.sonarsource.scanner.maven</groupId>
    <artifactId>sonar-maven-plugin</artifactId>
    <version>3.9.1.2184</version>
</plugin>

<plugin>
    <groupId>com.fortify.plugin</groupId>
    <artifactId>fortify-maven-plugin</artifactId>
    <version>1.1.0</version>
</plugin>
```

